## Part 2: Phase 2 — AI Agent Expansion (MCP Integration)

### Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[React Frontend] -->|REST| B[Spring Boot REST API]
    B --> C[(PostgreSQL)]
    B --> D[Spring AI / Groq]
    
    E[Desktop AI Assistant / Claude Desktop] -->|MCP Protocol| F[Spring AI MCP Server]
    G[NGO's AI Agent] -->|MCP Protocol| F
    F --> C
    F --> B
    
    A -->|WebSocket| B
    A -->|Chatbot UI| H[Support Bot MCP Client]
    H -->|MCP Protocol| F
```

The **MCP Server** is hosted **within the same Spring Boot application** as a new module. It is secured by an MCP-specific API key (separate from JWT). External agents connect to it via stdin/stdout for local tools, or via SSE/HTTP for remote agents.

---

### Backend Changes

#### [MODIFY] `pom.xml`

Add the Spring AI MCP Server dependency:

```xml
<!-- MCP Server — exposes tools for AI agents -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.ai</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-ai-mcp-server-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>
</dependency>
```

#### [MODIFY] `application.properties`

```properties
# ── MCP Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
spring.ai.mcp.server.name=resq-plate-mcp
spring.ai.mcp.server.version=1.0.0
spring.ai.mcp.server.type=SYNC
# For remote agents via SSE, enable the HTTP transport
spring.ai.mcp.server.sse.enabled=true
spring.ai.mcp.server.sse.api-key=${MCP_API_KEY}
```

