### Tool 5: Platform Admin Copilot (Data Retrieval Tools)

#### [NEW] `src/main/java/com/resq/ResQ_Plate/mcp/AdminCopilotTools.java`

A `@Service` class annotated with `@Tool` methods. Each method becomes an AI-callable function.

```java
@Service
public class AdminCopilotTools {

    @Tool(description = "Get a summary of food donations rescued this month, including total kg and meal count")
    public Map<String, Object> getMonthlyRescueSummary() { ... }

    @Tool(description = "Get a list of all donors and their total contributions, sorted by kg rescued")
    public List<Map<String, Object>> getDonorLeaderboard() { ... }

    @Tool(description = "Get count of donations by status (AVAILABLE, CLAIMED, COMPLETED, EXPIRED)")
    public Map<String, Long> getDonationStatusBreakdown() { ... }
    
    @Tool(description = "Get all donations expiring in the next N hours")
    public List<Map<String, Object>> getDonationsExpiringWithinHours(
        @ToolParam(description = "Number of hours to look ahead") int hours) { ... }
}
```

**How to use**: Connect Claude Desktop (or any MCP-compatible client) to this server. Ask: *"How many kg of food was rescued this month?"* The AI will call `getMonthlyRescueSummary()` and give you a natural language answer.

